# 4. あたたかな雰囲気の中で

Ena: Here, you can wear these pajamas. They should be pretty clean since I hardly ever use them.
Mafuyu: Thank you...
Mother's Voice: Ena! Dinner's ready!
Ena: Be right there! Let's go, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: Okay...
Ena: Wow, I'm starving... Mom, what did you make for dinner...?
Akito: I'm back.
Ena: Oh, Akito, welcome home.
Akito: Ugh...
Ena: What's with the attitude? I was just welcoming you home. And why are your eyes going all over the place? What's going on...?
Ena: Wait, that thing you're carrying... Isn't that from the new pancake shop that just opened up by the station...?!
Akito: Ugh... Why you of all people?
Ena: Hold on! You bought some for me too, right?!
Akito: Why would I do that? You honestly expect me to buy something for you every time I go to one of these places?
Ena: Excuse me? You're not the only person in this house with a sweet tooth, so you could show a little more courtesy.
Ena: Actually, on second thought, that means you would've had to buy some for Mafuyu too...
Akito: What...?
Mafuyu: Pardon me. Um... You're Akito, yes?
Akito: Oh, hello... Sorry, we didn't mean for you to see that.
Mafuyu: No, I apologize for the sudden intrusion. Some things happened today that led to me staying over for the night.
Akito: Ah, I see. We don't have much to offer here, but please make yourself at home.
Ena: (Geez, enough with the faces, you two...)
Mother: Alright, all of you, come sit down before dinner gets cold!
Ena: Be right there.
Mother: That includes you, Mafuyu. Please, join us.
Mafuyu: Thank you very much.
Mafuyu: But, you're too kind. You've already agreed to let me stay over for the night and to also be given dinner on top of that...
Ena: You really don't have to feel so apologetic, you know?
Ena: Oh, we're having Salisbury steaks today? Nice! They look delicious!
Ena: Hang on... Mom! How many times do I have to tell you?! No glazed carrots!
Mother: Stop complaining and eat what's on your plate.
Mother: Also, Mafuyu, Ena's right. Please feel free to make yourself comfortable.
Mother: More importantly, I hope what I've made is to your liking.
Mafuyu: Yes, everything looks delicious.
Ena: Then, want these glazed carrots?
Akito: Pushing the things you don't like onto Asahina would just bother her, don't you think?
Ena: In my hands, they'll go to waste. So, isn't it better to give them to someone who enjoys eating them?
Akito: I'm saying that you should quit complaining and just eat them.
Akito: It's okay for you to refuse, Asahina.
Mafuyu: Hehe. Thank you.
Ena: What? Says you, Mr. Picky...
Ena: Or do you want them instead? In that case, here, they're all yours!
Akito: Hey! Stop it!
Ena: All I'm saying is that you should stop complaining and just eat them.
Akito: And I was talking about stuff that's on your own plate.
Mother: That's enough, you two. Your Salisbury steaks are getting cold!
Akito & Ena: Yes, Mom...
Ena: Anyway, let's eat.
Mother: Please don't hesitate and eat as much as you'd like, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: Thank you. And this Salisbury steak's very good.
Ena: (Even though you don't know what anything tastes like? You really don't have to put on your honor student act in front of her...)
Akito: It's been a while since we last had these.
Mother: When I heard that Ena was having a friend over, I couldn't help myself and decided to put together a little feast.
Mafuyu: Again, thank you for letting me stay on such short notice. I also really like Salisbury steaks, so I'm glad you made them for us.
Mother: Hehe. I'm happy to hear that. By the way, you go to a different school, yes? How did you two meet?
Akito: You're both in the same music group making songs together, right?
Mafuyu: Oh, um...
Ena: Yeah, but keep that to yourself. Mafuyu's mom doesn't exactly approve.
Mother: Oh, really? I think it's wonderful that you make your own music.
Mafuyu: It's just... I have to study and...
Mother: Ah, because entrance exams are coming up. In that case, I somewhat understand your mother's concern.
Mother: Still, it's important to stop and smell the roses, you know? Or would your mother not like me saying that...?
Mother: In my case, I'm worried about Ena since she's doing what she loves but always seems so frustrated.
Ena: Guh...
Mafuyu: (She's worried...?)
Mafuyu: (I suppose that's only natural...)
Mother: But what I say won't change who my children are. Which is why I believe it's important for her to live her life the way she likes.
Mafuyu: What...?
Mafuyu: (The way she likes...? But...)
Mafuyu's Mother: No, that's okay. If there's something you truly wish to do, I plan on being there to support you.
Mafuyu's Mother: I'm worried about you, so I can't help but state how I feel... However, Mafuyu, it's ultimately your life to live...
Mafuyu's Mother: So you're free to do whatever you like...
Mafuyu: (She seems so different from Mom...)
Mafuyu: (Why is that...?)
Ena: Yeah, I'm always gonna do whatever I like regardless of what anyone says.
Mother: Yes, yes, I know. But don't forget to study a little too along the way.
Akito: Yeah, you could learn a lot from Asahina.
Ena: Ugh! Shut up! Also, Akito, you're one to talk since you usually just barely get by on your test.
Akito: Hey, as long as I'm not failing. Don't forget that I study with my teammates before tests and stuff.
Mother: Well, I'd actually rather have you aim for at least an average score, though.
Akito: Guh... M-Maybe when practice ends early for a change...
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (I knew it...)
Mafuyu: (This house feels so different...)
Mafuyu: (At my house, we usually have very settled discussions during dinner and hardly ever argue...)
Mafuyu: (However, despite all this arguing, Ena's house doesn't feel cold or distant at all...)
Mother: I apologize for us getting into such a heated discussion, Mafuyu. Especially after inviting you into our home...
Mafuyu: No, that's okay... I also discuss my studies with my parents on a regular basis.
Mother: You do? That's wonderful. If possible, would you mind tutoring these two from time to time?
Mafuyu: Yes, of course. Ena, Akito, please let me know if you ever need any help with studying.
Akito: Th-Thank you very much...
Ena: I'll pass. Mafuyu tutoring me sounds like torture.
Akito: I'm sure she'd feel the same way about being your tutor.
Ena: Excuse me?! I'm not you! I can get good grades if I try!
Ena: What's this, Akito? You haven't touched the carrots that you like so much.
Ena: Here, I'll give you some more since I've got plenty left on my plate.
Akito: Hey, I said quit it.
Mafuyu: (What is this...?)
Mafuyu: (My chest feels so...light...)
Mafuyu: (This house looks no different from mine, but something about it is.)
Mafuyu: (What is that difference exactly...?)
